00073   bool
00074   UVar::invariant() const
00075   {
00076     if (vardata)
00077       return true;
00078     else
00079     {
00080       // FIXME: this special case should be put in doc.
00081       echo ("Unable to locate variable %s in hashtable. "
00082             "UVars being UObject attributes must be binded to be used "
00083             "in UObject C++ code. Use UBindVar. "
00084             "In any other case, this can be a memory problem. "
00085             "Please report bug.\n",
00086              name.c_str());
00087       return false;
00088     }
00089   }

00127   UVar&
00128   uvalue_caster<UVar>::operator() (UValue& v)
00129   {
00130     if (v.type == DATA_VOID)
00131       return *((UVar*)v.storage);
00132     if (v.type != DATA_STRING)
00133       return *(UVar*)0;
00134     UVar* var = new UVar(*v.stringValue);
00135     getCurrentContext()->addCleanup(var);
00136     var->set_temp(true);
00137     return *var;
00138   }
